## cpus

The `/cpus` node is required by all device trees. It contains child nodes representing each processor in the system.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi */
cpus {
    #address-cells = <2>;
    #size-cells = <0>;

    cpu0: cpu@0 {
        compatible = "arm,cortex-a510";
        device_type = "cpu";
        reg = <0x0 0x0>;
    };
};
```
